title: ICE with chumsky crate

labels.name: I-ICE
labels.description: Issue: The compiler panicked, giving an Internal Compilation Error (ICE) ❄️

labels.name: T-compiler
labels.description: Relevant to the compiler team, which will review and decide on the PR/issue.

body:
### Code #### Cargo.toml ``` [package] name = "ice-repro" version = "0.1.0" edition = "2021" # See more keys and their definitions at https://doc.rust-lang.org/cargo/reference/manifest.html [dependencies] chumsky = "0.7" ``` #### src/lib.rs ```Rust use chumsky::prelude::*; use chumsky::text::*; pub fn parser() -> impl Parser> { just("foo ") .to((|n: i64| n) as fn(i64) -> i64) .then(int(10)) .map(|(f, n): (fn(i64) -> i64, i64)| f(n)) } ``` ### Meta `rustc --version --verbose`: ``` rustc 1.57.0 (f1edd0429 2021-11-29) binary: rustc commit-hash: f1edd0429582dd29cccacaf50fd134b05593bd9c commit-date: 2021-11-29 host: x86_64-unknown-linux-gnu release: 1.57.0 LLVM version: 13.0.0 ``` **This bug does not appear to occur in beta or nightly** (`cargo 1.58.0-beta (7f08ace4f 2021-11-24)` and `cargo 1.59.0-nightly (fcef61230 2021-12-17)`). I'm not sure whether it's still useful to report here. ### Error output ``` WARN rustc_metadata::locator no metadata found: incompatible metadata version found:
